4.68/5  rDev +4.7%look: 4 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4.5Brew is quite dark, as expected; head is dark brown, with better size and retention than many standard Bomb!s I've had.
Aroma is like Bomb!, but laced with bourbon, as expected. Sweet coconut, vanilla, and bourbon give way to the waves of chocolate, coffee, and chilies.
Flavor follows: what is already a fantastically complex (yet flawlessly integrated) brew gets an extra dose of complexity. The sweet (and strong!) bourbon and slightly dull oak complement the standard chocolate and coffee notes from Bomb!, while the chilies, more subdued than in the regular version (no doubt due to the time spent aging), add more flavor than heat (of which there isn't much of note). The bourbon really is quite noticeable, yet is very smoothly integrated.
Other flavors of note: grape soda, caramel syrup, and toffee.
Mouthfeel is incredibly full; probably the chewiest BA stout I've ever had. The ABV is even more well hidden than in the regular Bomb! (which clocks in higher, but still).
It's truly remarkable how well everything comes together here. This is really like drinking a beer that is masquerading as a White Russian. Man, if you could drink this every day: why wouldn't you? 1,183 charactersRoguer, Sep 30, 2016
