4.43/5  rDev -0.9%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Poured from a bottle into a snifter, the beer is jet black, oily thick, and with a scant, wispy, surface coating of tan head. Aromas of heavily roasted coffee, rich vanilla and chocolate, subtle wood char and whiskey character, and subtle pepper spice. Flavors are chocolate and vanilla forward, with a quick follow of pepper heat. Very balanced, with notes of whiskey spice and warmth coming in, as well as some bitter roasted coffee in the backbone. Amazingly balanced on a smooth, creamy, chewy body. The beer has a solid aftertaste of chocolate, vanilla, and whiskey, with some of the chili heat amplifying the booze warmth starting to build. Layered and velvety smooth finish, with a rich chocolate, vanilla, and coffee linger. Really amazing beer! 753 charactersGarthDanielson, Aug 14, 2016
