3.92/5  rDev -12.3%look: 4.25 | smell: 4 | taste: 3.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 3.75Review is of a 5-6 month old bottle
Pours a pitch black body with a khaki colored head. Head retention and lacing were pretty good.
Smell is of cinnamon, vanilla, vegetal peppers, and sweet bourbon/oak. Hops are non existent and alcohol is prominent. Disappointed to not get a lot of coffee. 
Taste is of sweet chocolate syrup followed by hot vegetal peppers. Toasted oak and spice like nutmeg or cinnamon come through next. As in nose, I dont get any coffee, bummer. Alcohol is moderate for a barrel aged imperial stout. 
Mouthfeel is full with a nice creamy head. Carbonation is lively and peppers add a slight numbing tingle to the tongue. 
Overall this beer was nowhere near the original Bomb! Whisky muddled everything and peppers didnt taste as good as in the regular bomb. Coffee also was lacking in this version unfortunately. 839 charactersangelmonster, Jun 09, 2016
