4.75/5  rDev +6.3%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75AnotherImperial, May 21, 2016
3.85/5  rDev -13.9%look: 3.5 | smell: 4 | taste: 3.75 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 3.75Pours almost black, with a small, immediately disappearing dark brown head, leaving back a small, bubbly ring of lacing.
Smells of roasted coffee, which gets  a smoky quality, resulting from the chilies, blending beautifully into a fragile, less pronounced barrel spiciness. Rich toffee malts and a hint of molasses create the foundation in this, with all the adjuncts blending in on top, crowned by a whiff of flowery sweet vanilla.
Drinks very silk, with a nice interplay of oaken spices and the chilies dialing in for a hot, still pleasant finish. Drinks fairly easy for its higher abv, very well composed, while the beer's barrel addition is almost a bit subdued.
Begins with whipped cream, toffee, milk chocolate, a hint of molasses and bakers chocolate, from which the chilies evolve. They add a short, hot bite to the beer, with the chocolaty maltiness cutting through, which invites spicy and pleasantly dry Bourbon to the palate, adding to the chili warmth after the swallow. Finishes with a great mix of toffee, licorice and a faint Bourbon dryness, leaving earthen coffee on the palate.
Comes very well together, with all adjuncts blending perfectly well into the malty foundation of the beer. Its barrel treatment is a bit of a let down since it is a bit subdued. 1,279 charactersaleigator, May 21, 2016
