3.96/5  rDev -11.4%look: 3.75 | smell: 4 | taste: 4 | feel: 3.75 |  overall: 4From a 355 ml bottle to a tulip. Reviewed from notes dated March 9, 2016. 
A-The beer looks somewhat flat coming out of the bottle. A short, mocha colored head fades almost immediately and leaves no lacing. The beer is pitch black and still. Uninspiring, but not ugly to look at.
S-The aroma is well spiced with clearly identifiable chili notes, as well as vanilla, cocoa, and brewed coffee. The barrel is there, and it gives off some caramel and a certain boozy sweetness, but it doesn't overwhelm. Its not bad, but I don't like it as much as regular Bomb! Too much going on?
T-The taste is similar to the smell. The beer is quite sweet from start to finish with layers upon layers of adjuncts coming across my palate. Like normal Bomb! this is kind of a mess, but it is mostly enjoyable and the flavors play well. I'm not sure that this beer needs the addition of barrel aging.
M-My bottle was a touch under-carbonated. What little carbonation there was was creamy. Medium heft for the style.
O-I like regular Bomb! a lot. There is so much going on in the normal version and the flavors work together well, so I was excited to try this one (although I have had a few bottles that tasted overly vegetal, as if the chilis went bad or something). With my expectations set high, this beer was a bit of letdown. It is a GOOD beer, but the addition of barrel aging doesn't help make a better Bomb! 1,398 charactersspoony, Apr 30, 2016
