4.51/5  rDev +0.9%look: 5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5Looks on point. Smells on point. Smells more than on point. Fudgey brownie meets oaken, bourbon spice with a little extra spice on top. The smell is thick and sticky and sweet. It smells like some boozy dessert treat. Pretty phenomenal. 
A bit of tartness in the taste though. I hadn't heard that in others descriptions to me. It doesn't harm the beer really and I keep sipping along. Continue to get a huge brownie, baker's chocolate profile. Faint lingering spicy chile notes are the only remnants of what I recall from the base beer, which I've gone a while without drinking. 
There's an excellent interaction between the gooey chocolatey flavors and a clean whiskey/bourbon flavor and this is complemented further by some thick caramel, tobacco, oak and raisin. The initial tartness has all but disappeared, so maybe I imagined it. 
As for how this drinks, it's big, full in the mouth, gooey, and booze present, though there's no offensive or overwhelming heat here. A tinge of tartness does occasionally sneak in. 
This is highly enjoyable. Full-flavored, rich-drinking and, again, dessert-like. 1,104 charactersONovoMexicano, Mar 24, 2016
