4.6/5  rDev +2.9%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.75Serving: 12 oz. bottle poured into a Cigar City snifter. Bottled on 1/7/16, making this about 1.5 months old.
A: Pours a medium body, pitch black. Some soft bubbles coming up along the edges leaving a faint, tan head.
S: Vanilla, cinnamon, spice, nutmeg, pepper skin. All of it wrapped in a subtle layer of whiskey and rye. 
T: Cocoa, nutmeg, cayenne, vanilla, cinnamon, rum, whiskey, oak, char. 
M: A bit on the thin side, but not watery. Decent carbonation. Alcohol well-hidden. Most of the kick and spice is buried in the barrel-aging.
O: Been wanting to try this one for a while. Haven't been all too much impressed with Prairie's output as of late, but figured one of their most well-known beers could redeem that. Bomb! is a good beer, but maybe not a great beer. I think it falls short because it's a bit muted and doesn't quite pop like it's competitors in the style. Barrel-aging an already muted beer doesn't sound like a good idea, but I think they pull it off here. This one is very balanced, drinkable, smooth, and somehow the flavors pop just a little more in the base beer. I think that's mostly because a lot of the rough edges get smoothed out over time. This is a great beer, and one of the best offerings from Prairie.
Recommendation: Not as hard to find as you might think, so definitely grab this if you can, it's well worth it. 1,355 charactersSparty1224, Feb 25, 2016
