4.57/5  rDev +2.2%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.512oz bottle poured into a Prairie Artisan Ales Prairie Dog teku glass. Enjoyed on 2.10.16, reviewed from Tasting Journal. 
The beer pours a jet black color, thick, oily, viscous and inky with a thin finger of khaki head, low retention and no lace. The aroma is wonderful, loads of coffee, strong but layered barrel character, light spice, tons of chocolate, chewy oak, char and hints of vanilla. The flavors are impeccable, bursting with coffee, spice is there but integrated really well, vanilla bean and semi sweet chocolate pop out well with bourbon and charred oak. Brown sugar and caramel richness linger well offering a very decadent total package that has a nice liveliness from the heat. The mouthfeel is great, chewy and thick, full bodied, very smooth with lower carbonation with a silky finish that has some light warmth.
Verdict: A stellar barrel aged stout from Prairie Artisan Ales. Great complexity, nice balance and excellent coffee character. The base beer is already great, but this elevates it to a completely different level. Outstanding beer. 1,065 characterskevanb, Feb 20, 2016
