4/5  rDev -10.5%look: 3.5 | smell: 4 | taste: 4 | feel: 3.75 |  overall: 4.25Pours a soul devouring black, which is attenuated by the lack of head to offset the darkness of this beer. I poured at a 45 degree angle for about half the bottle and then turned the glass perpendicular, and still didn't get much of any fizz. No lacing sprouted out either. Bourbon and oak come out first in the nose, a sweet, complex sampling of malt and vanilla aromas come out in the background. A sip opens up a smooth blast of vanilla and sweet malt, with a little bourbon booze burn on the back end. The booze taste is well balanced, and doesn't make it difficult to drink at all. Mouth feel doesn't make it super fun to drink, although it isn't bad. It isn't as thick or creamy as a regular Bomb! or other imperial stouts on the market. It feels a bit thin overall. Overall, it's still a great beer. Plenty is happening, it's all just very subdued. I do fancy the artwork though.
As per how it compares with a regular Bomb! It adds a little complexity over the regular Bomb! while pulling out some of the big, bold flavors of the Bomb! Mouth feel is better with the regular Bomb. Both are great beers, but I really think Bomb trumps the BA version in most ways. I prefer the artwork on this one.
Served in a 12oz snifter. 1,230 charactersHarrison8, Feb 19, 2016
