4.57/5  rDev +2.2%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.5L: Opaque chestnut brown and inky black hues; microscopic tan head laces the perimeter of the glass and quickly recedes
S: Milk chocolate on the nose with subtle hints of vanilla and mocha
T: Rush of hazelnut, dark cocoa, and vanilla is aptly met by a slight alcoholic flavoring from the barrel aging; the finish is a healthy, pleasant chocolate (almost like a pudding aftertaste) taste
F: Medium to medium-thick mouthfeel that is in line with a thicker Grade B maple syrup - not the thickest mouthfeel I've ever encountered, but on point and enjoyable
O: This is a well executed variant on one of my go-to favorite stouts. To me there was less of a lingering alcohol flavor that sometimes burdens BA stouts, but with the aging I thought the stout took on a smoother and more luxurious flavor depth vs. regular Bomb! Overall I immensely enjoyed the refined taste. My only fault is that the vanilla and chilies were slightly muted - however this lends itself to a smoother experience all around. At the end of the day this was a great variation of the base beer and one worth seeking out. 1,087 charactersFireman_RK, Feb 16, 2016
