4.65/5  rDev +4%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Poured slightly cooled into a room temperature tulip.
A: Pours a rich, dark brown with a slight tan head that quickly dissipates into a ring that still manages a little lacing.
S: Whiskey and roast notes are met with some chili and vanilla tones.  Boozey.  A little intimidating, but not enough to give up a barrel aged version of a fantastic beer.
T: An amazing concert of chocolate, caramel, coffee and vanilla with a little whiskey and chili notes on the back end.  The flavors are big and bold, but not overwhelming and riff on one another perfectly.  There is a little alcohol warming on the back end, but isn't too hot.  The lively chili flavor settles on the palate.
M: Like the big flavors, this beer has some heft to it but it's one you want to wade through.  Not much carbonation to it, but enough to keep it lively.  
O: I love BOMB! and this is on another level.  A fantastic beer, a must have and one you should keep in your closet.  With the barrel aging and impressive ABV, it'll be just fine in your Bat Cave for a while until you get around to drinking it. 1,078 charactersFBGordon, Feb 12, 2016
