An oily, opaque dark brown/black, with a small beige head that diminishes into a cluster of bubbles after only a moment. Spotty lacing (close to a red wine in that regard). Nose is classic Bomb! with a bit more "oomph" on the vanilla and cacao front, presumably from the barrel. Flavor profile brings a lot more cinnamon to the forefront, delicious rich mocha, and that classic Bomb! subtle chile heat in the finish. Feel is nice, somewhere between moderate and thick, not quite as viscous as I would like from a BA stout, but a bit chewier than regular Bomb! I'm an unabashed Bomb! fanboy, admittedly, but this is spectacular. I need more. 688 charactersmarkgugs, Jan 26, 2015
4.1/5  rDev -8.3%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4dleiner, Jan 24, 2015
4.85/5  rDev +8.5%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75CaptainFleeker, Jan 23, 2015
3.67/5  rDev -17.9%look: 4 | smell: 3.75 | taste: 3.5 | feel: 3.75 |  overall: 3.75Thanks Sonny, cool to do this after Pirate. Tampa review dump. Full review to IPad during drinking of this ale.
A- Right on par with the other Bombs as far as the sludgey midnight black body and dark tan frothy cap. Medium ring remains after decent retention leaving only spotty lacing.
S- Whiskey barrel is smoothed out but brings more strength than the rum one in Pirate. Heavy tannic oak has me worried for the flavor but nice Bourbon vanilla. Roasty and dark but overall rather tame when compared to other Bombs.
T- Heavy vanilla and cocoa but also a huge amount of woody tannic blackened oak. This wood overshadows an absolute beast of a base beer as only hints of cocoa, peppers, dark coffee and charred grain can make it through. Coca cola and spicy whiskey notes.
MF- Thick body perhaps a bit thinned out by the aging and Bourbon. Medium carbonation gives off just a bit of frothy and slick oily texture. Oaky dark roast bitter finish. Slight chile and alcohol heat.
Probably my least favorite variant of this monstrous beer. The barrel just takes away from the great dessert like base and the wood is too much. Good idea but needs better execution. 1,162 characterscbutova, Jan 16, 2015
