3.78/5  rDev -15.4%look: 3.75 | smell: 3.75 | taste: 3.75 | feel: 4 |  overall: 3.75A:  Pours an opaque black color.  A minimal tan head rises to less than a finger.  No lace, which is to be expected.  Thick and viscous.
S:  Pretty simple.  Up front is milk chocolate and vanilla beans.  A bit of peppery heat in the background.
T:  Like the nose, all milk chocolate and vanilla beans.  Really sweet.  A hint of some pepper spice and heat in the background.  Maybe a mix of peppers and alcohol.  Any barrel presents is nowhere to be seen.
M/D:  A full, viscous and thick body.  Low carbonation, but not under carbonated at all.  With as big of a body that is here, it is never overwhelming, which is impressive.  Enjoyable to sip on.  A good warmer.
I do like this.  The chocolate/vanilla/sweetness works really well, and the peppers from Bomb, like always are subtle but add just a bit of heat.  Though the barrel character is almost nonexistent.  A barrel presents can certainly be done at overwhelming levels, but here it is almost nothing.  That disappoints me a bit.  Maybe not worth the cost, but enjoyable for what it is. 1,045 characterschamp103, Nov 20, 2014
